Package application.model

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    WorkLoad
    Holds the data of a single workload in an associative manner.
    WorkLoadDistributor
    The WorkLoadDistributor is used to distribute the WorkLoadLaneEntrys onto the resources aka WorkLoadLanes.
    WorkLoadLane
    Can hold WorkLoadLaneEntrys and can determine if they are overlapping with the already added WorkLoadLaneEntrys.
    WorkLoadLaneEntry
    Holds the WorkLoad that it was derived from, and interval begin/end, the amount of resources used by the WorkLoad and a Color to display the WorkLoadLaneEntry with.
    WorkLoadProfile
    Contains the Labels for data lines, the value-separator used for reading in data and a boolean that determines the behaviour when there are more data entries than labels
    WorkLoadTrace
    Represents an workload-trace.
